483
00:55:55,068 --> 00:55:56,399
Did you see Ranjan?

484
00:55:59,839 --> 00:56:00,828
How long it's going on?

485
00:56:03,843 --> 00:56:05,401
How many messages
have you sent him?

486
00:56:06,079 --> 00:56:07,171
l didn't get you, sir.

487
00:56:07,380 --> 00:56:09,143
Which side we are coming?
How many in the squad?

488
00:56:10,083 --> 00:56:11,311
Sir, l didn't...

489
00:56:14,387 --> 00:56:15,319
Tell me now.

490
00:56:16,923 --> 00:56:19,323
How dare you manhandle
a police lnspector?

491
00:56:22,862 --> 00:56:24,489
Aren't you ashamed to call
yourself a police man?

492
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:25,924
l'll not care even if you're
my senior officer.

493
00:56:26,132 --> 00:56:26,996
Don't see.

494
00:56:30,370 --> 00:56:32,304
Where is Veera?
- l don't know sir.

495
00:56:37,076 --> 00:56:38,839
Take me to Veeraiah.

496
00:57:02,168 --> 00:57:05,535
ln 6 months or a year,
you'll get transferred,

497
00:57:05,905 --> 00:57:07,031
we've to live here only.

498
00:57:07,841 --> 00:57:09,468
My brothers and sisters
have to study here,

499
00:57:10,577 --> 00:57:12,135
who will protect them?

500
00:57:12,345 --> 00:57:16,145
He's right sir.
- Will you work for Veera for that?

501
00:57:16,349 --> 00:57:17,577
He too is right.

502
00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:03,528
l know the way but don't know
if Veera will be there or not.

503
00:58:03,897 --> 00:58:07,355
Just show us the way,
we'll find Veera.

504
00:58:24,484 --> 00:58:27,180
Check what happened...

505
00:58:30,156 --> 00:58:31,453
The tank is open here.

506
00:58:31,691 --> 00:58:34,455
Move...move...move...

507
00:58:37,263 --> 00:58:38,287
Sugar!

508
00:58:38,965 --> 00:58:40,057
Sugar in diesel tank.

509
00:58:40,266 --> 00:58:43,133
ln all three trucks, how could
they do it while on move?

510
00:58:52,345 --> 00:58:53,471
l don't know sir.

511
00:58:54,948 --> 00:58:56,973
Villagers from neighbouring
hamlet, shepherds.

512
00:58:57,183 --> 00:58:58,912
Seeking permission to
cross the camp.

513
01:00:02,415 --> 01:00:04,542
This is SP's tent.

514
01:00:24,437 --> 01:00:25,631
We've a problem here.

515
01:00:26,672 --> 01:00:28,230
They have sabotaged the trucks.

516
01:02:02,502 --> 01:02:04,834
<i>The meat is in the stove...</i>

517
01:02:05,204 --> 01:02:07,468
<i>Pour me a glass of liquor...</i>

518
01:02:07,673 --> 01:02:10,107
<i>The girl looks at you and yearns...</i>

519
01:02:10,309 --> 01:02:12,607
<i>Oh man...</i>
<i>exchange garlands with the bride...</i>

520
01:02:14,090 --> 01:02:17,753
What shall l cut?
Tongue or nose?

521
01:02:22,365 --> 01:02:23,832
How about ear?

522
01:02:50,827 --> 01:02:53,557
Catch him...tonsure his head.

523
01:02:54,130 --> 01:02:57,258
No brother...
l beg you, please leave me.

524
01:03:01,337 --> 01:03:02,804
Tonsure his head.

525
01:03:08,044 --> 01:03:10,342
Chakkare lost the challenge
with Singanna.

526
01:03:11,481 --> 01:03:14,177
He challenged we can't come
back alive from police camps.

527
01:03:14,384 --> 01:03:16,443
Tonsure!

528
01:03:19,155 --> 01:03:24,092
l saw your SP's tent.

529
01:03:25,161 --> 01:03:28,790
He keeps...a photo.

530
01:03:30,333 --> 01:03:32,392
Not yours but mine.

531
01:03:33,102 --> 01:03:35,400
ln a villain's pose,
like old screen villain MN Nambiar.

532
01:03:36,573 --> 01:03:37,904
Boys!

533
01:03:39,576 --> 01:03:41,601
A demon's photo in SP's tent.

534
01:03:46,182 --> 01:03:47,547
Take him on a donkey.

535
01:03:49,085 --> 01:03:50,052
Catch him!

536
01:04:02,465 --> 01:04:08,131
<i>Chop them if they draw a line...</i>

537
01:04:10,874 --> 01:04:16,278
<i>Break it when they put a fence...</i>

538
01:04:18,047 --> 01:04:22,347
<i>Until yesterday the law was in your</i>
<i>hands from today it will be ours...</i>

539
01:04:38,401 --> 01:04:40,232
<i>We were bending down like a bow...</i>

540
01:04:40,436 --> 01:04:42,927
<i>Now we will stand straight</i>
<i>like an arrow...</i>

541
01:04:44,908 --> 01:04:48,469
<i>If they ask for a share of your food,</i>
<i>serve it in plates...</i>

542
01:04:48,678 --> 01:04:52,546
<i>If they ask for a share of your fortune,</i>
<i>roll down their heads...</i>

543
01:04:52,916 --> 01:04:56,875
<i>The land will never bow down</i>
<i>to the rules of it's neighbours...</i>

544
01:04:57,086 --> 01:05:00,954
<i>The sky will not listen when the</i>
<i>cloud comes and makes noise...</i>

545
01:05:01,157 --> 01:05:05,287
<i>No one can take away the</i>
<i>land of our ancestors...</i>

546
01:05:38,094 --> 01:05:41,928
<i>We belong to a race that tames</i>
<i>a snake and feed it cow's milk...</i>

547
01:05:42,131 --> 01:05:46,033
<i>Try doing a wrong, and</i>
<i>you will know our other side...</i>

548
01:05:46,235 --> 01:05:50,103
<i>We are warriors</i>
<i>born in the jungles...</i>

549
01:05:50,306 --> 01:05:54,140
<i>ln a bull fight, the intestine that</i>
<i>hangs out is our garland of victory...</i>

550
01:05:54,344 --> 01:05:58,610
<i>The only fortune left by</i>
<i>the old man is bravery...</i>

551
01:06:53,436 --> 01:06:57,338
<i>Our air will smell of fried fish...</i>

552
01:06:57,540 --> 01:07:02,102
<i>Our stream water will give you</i>
<i>the kick of a country liquor...</i>

553
01:07:02,311 --> 01:07:06,008
<i>A married man will</i>
<i>live a barren life...</i>

554
01:07:06,215 --> 01:07:10,151
<i>A cactus plant does</i>
<i>not require rain...</i>

555
01:07:10,486 --> 01:07:14,354
<i>No one becomes poor</i>
<i>by loosing a penny..</i>

556
01:07:14,557 --> 01:07:18,391
<i>If our pride goes,</i>
<i>you lose everything...</i>

557
01:07:18,594 --> 01:07:22,496
<i>Our land is as much</i>
<i>our pride as our women...</i>

558
01:07:22,698 --> 01:07:27,032
<i>If you dig the forest,</i>
<i>even the red sands are our blood...</i>

559
01:08:32,468 --> 01:08:33,457
Look at me!

560
01:08:35,304 --> 01:08:36,498
Can you hear me?

561
01:08:38,808 --> 01:08:39,775
Open your eyes.

562
01:08:52,321 --> 01:08:58,692
Great! You can't escape
but helping him!

563
01:09:00,796 --> 01:09:02,263
What are you planning
to do with him?

564
01:09:02,465 --> 01:09:06,799
We'll send him to hell on a bull.

565
01:09:09,472 --> 01:09:11,497
Won't you see anyone as human?

566
01:09:14,844 --> 01:09:16,641
When will you people
stop taking vengeance?

567
01:09:16,846 --> 01:09:18,711
When will you rich people
stop your atrocities?

568
01:09:27,523 --> 01:09:30,822
You can see only
his uniform and his job.

569
01:09:31,594 --> 01:09:34,392
He has a heart and
good characters.

570
01:09:34,597 --> 01:09:36,827
He loves his mother
and fears her too.

571
01:09:37,433 --> 01:09:38,900
Why are you torturing him?

572
01:09:39,669 --> 01:09:40,863
Kill him instantly.

573
01:09:41,337 --> 01:09:44,500
Kill him...kill him...
shoot him...

574
01:09:44,707 --> 01:09:48,666
Don't think, shoot him.

575
01:09:51,380 --> 01:09:52,574
You want to know the reason, right?

576
01:09:54,517 --> 01:09:55,449
Answer her.

577
01:10:00,223 --> 01:10:01,588
A brave man, afraid of mother.

578
01:10:03,626 --> 01:10:05,253
A fool who respects women.

579
01:10:07,530 --> 01:10:09,430
What did you with Vennila?
Tell her.

580
01:10:14,804 --> 01:10:15,862
Who is Vennila?

581
01:10:16,806 --> 01:10:18,865
The girl who changed your fate.

582
01:10:22,445 --> 01:10:23,537
Who is Vennila?

583
01:10:23,879 --> 01:10:25,244
lsn't she asking you?

584
01:10:25,648 --> 01:10:26,774
Who is Vennila?

585
01:10:27,483 --> 01:10:28,780
My father's offspring.

586
01:10:31,254 --> 01:10:32,448
But not of my mother.

587
01:10:32,822 --> 01:10:34,551
My father's second wife's daughter.

588
01:10:35,391 --> 01:10:37,484
Clever and brave girl.

589
01:10:38,294 --> 01:10:40,455
The only one who isn't
afraid of Veera.

590
01:10:48,304 --> 01:10:50,329
She fell in love with a boy.

591
01:10:50,740 --> 01:10:52,298
He too is from
a rich family like you.

592
01:11:07,823 --> 01:11:12,692
Veera arranged their marriage
after much pleas and cajoling.

593
01:11:13,529 --> 01:11:16,987
That was the first marriage
in our family.

594
01:11:17,366 --> 01:11:18,833
You know how happy she was?

595
01:11:19,335 --> 01:11:29,438
<i>When lightning struck...</i>
<i>eyes are fluttering...</i>

596
01:11:29,879 --> 01:11:34,839
<i>The sinful mind yearns</i>
<i>for the girl...</i>

597
01:11:35,051 --> 01:11:42,423
<i>The dot on her forehead</i>
<i>has stuck to my heart...</i>

598
01:11:42,625 --> 01:11:47,085
Sister! Another sister is here
to put henna.

599
01:12:08,084 --> 01:12:09,711
You look great in sari
and blouse.

600
01:12:09,919 --> 01:12:13,548
You wanted to see the lion,
so here l am.

601
01:12:14,523 --> 01:12:16,650
You came like a coward dancing
as a girl among women.

602
01:12:16,859 --> 01:12:17,757
So you managed.

603
01:12:17,960 --> 01:12:20,087
Had my brothers seen you,
you'll be dead.

604
01:12:20,696 --> 01:12:23,563
l know Judo and Karate,
learnt it in school.

605
01:12:24,433 --> 01:12:27,561
White belt holder,
no man can beat me.

606
01:12:29,472 --> 01:12:30,939
No man can beat you?

607
01:12:36,379 --> 01:12:36,845
What do you say now?

608
01:12:37,046 --> 01:12:39,514
What's this?
Have you gone mad?

609
01:12:40,383 --> 01:12:41,350
You said no man can
dare touch you.

610
01:12:41,550 --> 01:12:42,915
Close the door,
someone may see me.

611
01:12:45,855 --> 01:12:47,914
lf your folks see me, l'm dead.

612
01:12:48,124 --> 01:12:49,113
Show your Karate prowess.

613
01:12:49,492 --> 01:12:52,086
Mad girl!
Don't open the door.

614
01:12:52,561 --> 01:12:54,791
Why? ls the groom afraid?

615
01:12:56,699 --> 01:12:58,724
She-devil! Listen to me.

616
01:12:58,934 --> 01:13:01,095
Shouldn't the world know
that you're a wrestler?

617
01:13:04,407 --> 01:13:05,601
Bloody!

618
01:13:05,941 --> 01:13:07,966
Why are you using bad words?
- Shouldn't l?

619
01:13:08,177 --> 01:13:09,439
Hide!
- Why?

620
01:13:09,645 --> 01:13:11,169
My brother.
- Where?

621
01:13:11,480 --> 01:13:12,174
Hide l say.

622
01:13:12,715 --> 01:13:13,773
Where do you want me to go?

623
01:13:15,851 --> 01:13:17,182
Should your brother come now?

624
01:13:18,988 --> 01:13:19,955
l'm dead.

625
01:13:20,723 --> 01:13:22,122
Open the door.
- Hide l say.

626
01:13:22,491 --> 01:13:24,118
No, l can't open the door now.
- Where's the back door?

627
01:13:25,060 --> 01:13:26,550
Who is inside?

628
01:13:26,762 --> 01:13:29,026
Who else will be there?
l and my shadow.

629
01:13:29,432 --> 01:13:32,799
Someone came to apply henna,
l know it.

630
01:13:33,436 --> 01:13:37,395
l'm changing.
- How can you change with henna?

631
01:13:37,606 --> 01:13:39,198
That's him!
- Oh my God!

632
01:13:41,811 --> 01:13:44,405
Brother-in-law!
What are you doing here?

633
01:13:44,613 --> 01:13:46,513
lt's not his fault,
l asked him to come.

634
01:13:46,916 --> 01:13:47,974
He came running here.

635
01:13:48,717 --> 01:13:50,207
l challenged him to dare come here.

636
01:13:51,854 --> 01:13:53,481
So, you've come in skirt
and half sari.

637
01:13:53,689 --> 01:13:55,020
What are you doing among women?

638
01:13:55,758 --> 01:13:57,749
Just like that...
- He held my hand.

639
01:13:58,561 --> 01:13:59,084
Who?

640
01:14:04,533 --> 01:14:06,524
Come down.

641
01:14:07,837 --> 01:14:08,735
Come.

642
01:14:16,479 --> 01:14:18,003
With which hand you
held my sister's hand?

643
01:14:20,082 --> 01:14:21,242
Don't harm him.

644
01:14:21,617 --> 01:14:23,517
Singarasu brother promised
to buy a bike as dowry.

645
01:14:23,719 --> 01:14:25,186
lt'll be like circus if he rides
bike with one hand.

646
01:14:25,554 --> 01:14:26,816
Should've thought about it earlier?

647
01:14:28,624 --> 01:14:29,249
Which hand?

648
01:14:30,960 --> 01:14:31,984
Which hand?

649
01:14:42,938 --> 01:14:43,996
Open your eyes.

650
01:14:45,674 --> 01:14:46,766
See the watch.

651
01:14:47,610 --> 01:14:49,976
Still 48 hours for the marriage.

652
01:14:51,614 --> 01:14:53,673
Till then keep your hand safely
with yourself.

653
01:14:54,183 --> 01:14:56,242
lf not you may have to
tie the knot with one hand.

654
01:14:58,621 --> 01:14:59,144
Go now.

655
01:15:01,557 --> 01:15:02,216
Go!

656
01:15:03,826 --> 01:15:07,728
Tell him, if not l think
he'll stay here only.

657
01:15:13,802 --> 01:15:14,268
Coward!

658
01:15:17,806 --> 01:15:21,765
Garland the goat!
- 101st man!

659
01:15:32,721 --> 01:15:37,522
<i>The meat is in the stove...</i>
<i>Pour me a glass of liquor...</i>

660
01:15:37,893 --> 01:15:40,191
<i>The girl looks at you and yearns...</i>

661
01:15:40,563 --> 01:15:42,622
<i>Oh man...</i>
<i>exchange garlands with the bride...</i>

662
01:15:42,831 --> 01:15:45,026
<i>The decked up girl is red</i>
<i>like an apple...</i>

663
01:15:45,234 --> 01:15:48,203
<i>And the guy is dark like</i>
<i>a blackberry...</i>

664
01:15:48,571 --> 01:15:53,634
<i>Oh girl, first exchange your garland...</i>
<i>And then change your attire...</i>

665
01:16:08,924 --> 01:16:11,722
<i>When you look at her</i>
<i>she seems like Janaki...</i>

666
01:16:11,927 --> 01:16:14,225
<i>But she is of Soorpanaka</i>
<i>descent in the bed...</i>

667
01:16:34,950 --> 01:16:40,252
<i>The girl looks small like a lemon</i>
<i>but she is very talkative...</i>

668
01:16:41,624 --> 01:16:42,921
<i>Let's the drums beat...</i>
<i>Let this flower blossom...</i>

669
01:16:47,997 --> 01:16:57,770
<i>As his sisters-in-law hold the</i>
<i>umbrella, the groom arrives...</i>

670
01:16:58,073 --> 01:17:02,772
<i>As her sister-in-law holds</i>
<i>the saree, the bride arrives...</i>

671
01:17:02,978 --> 01:17:06,209
<i>Let the marriage band play...</i>

672
01:17:41,050 --> 01:17:44,042
Father told me to seek
your blessings.

673
01:17:46,155 --> 01:17:47,816
No cries and melodrama please.

674
01:17:49,858 --> 01:17:53,988
As if you're great Sivaji Ganesan,
to make every girl cry on seeing brother.

675
01:17:56,699 --> 01:17:57,927
Brother-in-law knows it, right?

676
01:18:00,369 --> 01:18:02,337
Once given goods will
not be taken back.

677
01:18:04,373 --> 01:18:05,169
Brother.

678
01:18:10,312 --> 01:18:11,176
Please come.

679
01:18:26,328 --> 01:18:29,195
People like you're not allowed.

680
01:18:31,266 --> 01:18:33,359
Your kinsman invited us,
we came to bless the couple.

681
01:18:33,736 --> 01:18:34,361
Bless them?

682
01:18:39,074 --> 01:18:45,877
<i>Son-in-law...new son-in-law...</i>
<i>our son-in-law...</i>

683
01:18:49,418 --> 01:18:50,817
Move...give way.

684
01:18:51,019 --> 01:18:54,716
<i>Play the band...clap your hands...</i>
<i>sing and dance...make merry...</i>

685
01:19:02,264 --> 01:19:06,894
l beg you sir, please don't do it.

686
01:19:11,206 --> 01:19:12,400
We beg you sir, spare them.

687
01:19:14,777 --> 01:19:16,244
Leave them sir.

688
01:19:33,962 --> 01:19:35,088
Brother!!

689
01:19:46,308 --> 01:19:48,105
Dev will never shoot without
a valid reason.

690
01:19:52,281 --> 01:19:53,771
l'm sure the mistake
will not be his.

691
01:20:00,155 --> 01:20:01,281
lt was all my mistake.

692
01:20:06,295 --> 01:20:07,785
Eight people were pulling me.

693
01:20:13,168 --> 01:20:15,136
But still l shouldn't have
left Vennila alone.

694
01:20:17,272 --> 01:20:18,364
lt should've struck to my mind.

695
01:20:19,508 --> 01:20:20,873
l should've known it.

696
01:20:23,078 --> 01:20:25,376
l didn't expect her husband will
escape on seeing the police.

697
01:20:34,122 --> 01:20:41,324
The man who's afraid of mother
took my sister to police station.

698
01:20:47,169 --> 01:20:53,404
You can't go out from here till you
tell the whereabouts of your brother.

699
01:21:04,987 --> 01:21:09,185
Will you tell on your own?
l'll not show mercy on girl too.

700
01:21:09,892 --> 01:21:12,190
Open your mouth.
Tell me.

701
01:21:14,396 --> 01:21:19,265
You're a police man, aren't you?
Sniff and find him.

702
01:21:22,905 --> 01:21:24,031
l'll cut it.

703
01:21:24,907 --> 01:21:28,035
He dragged her to the station.
Wasn't it you who took her to station?

704
01:21:28,243 --> 01:21:29,369
You took her, right?

705
01:22:04,346 --> 01:22:05,506
Are you hurt seriously?

706
01:22:07,115 --> 01:22:08,241
Aren't you able to talk?

707
01:22:12,454 --> 01:22:16,356
No problem,
you can't argue with me.

708
01:22:18,160 --> 01:22:22,187
l can say anything,
you can't answer me.

709
01:22:26,568 --> 01:22:28,365
Did you see my new husband,
sister-in-law?

710
01:22:30,038 --> 01:22:31,437
He ran away in fear.

711
01:22:33,709 --> 01:22:35,267
He ran away leaving me behind.

712
01:22:37,145 --> 01:22:39,113
Who wants such an husband, brother?

713
01:22:42,084 --> 01:22:43,676
Why did l wish to marry?

714
01:22:46,989 --> 01:22:48,718
l should've remained
unmarried like you.

715
01:22:55,263 --> 01:22:57,356
Who are these police bastards?

716
01:23:02,437 --> 01:23:05,531
Who are they to ruin my life?

717
01:23:12,514 --> 01:23:13,572
l wasn't scared.

718
01:23:20,122 --> 01:23:21,419
Your new husband has run away,

719
01:23:24,593 --> 01:23:27,494
they asked who would l wish to
spend the first night with, brother?

720
01:23:34,036 --> 01:23:36,004
l used all bad words.

721
01:23:37,639 --> 01:23:40,335
l begged them saying it's sin.

