969
01:55:31,117 --> 01:55:33,517
l'm back, right?
What else you want?

970
01:55:38,525 --> 01:55:39,583
Where is he hiding?

971
01:55:42,696 --> 01:55:46,097
Did you come for me or for him?

972
01:55:49,636 --> 01:55:51,604
He escaped hiding
behind a woman.

973
01:55:52,973 --> 01:55:55,601
Forget about him, Dev.
- l'll come back for you.

974
01:56:02,315 --> 01:56:03,339
Let's go home.

975
01:56:10,323 --> 01:56:11,449
Shall we go home?

976
01:56:41,287 --> 01:56:42,185
Did he beat you?

977
01:56:47,761 --> 01:56:48,989
Did he scare you?

978
01:56:51,531 --> 01:56:52,327
No.

979
01:56:59,372 --> 01:57:00,339
Did he touch you?

980
01:57:06,212 --> 01:57:07,679
lf anything had happened...

981
01:57:16,222 --> 01:57:18,087
He kept you in captive
for 14 days.

982
01:57:18,792 --> 01:57:20,623
14 days and 14 nights.

983
01:57:22,796 --> 01:57:24,286
l can understand
what you're asking.

984
01:57:25,231 --> 01:57:27,597
Look at me.
Can't you see it yourself?

985
01:57:33,473 --> 01:57:35,202
Are you ready for
a lie detector test?

986
01:57:36,242 --> 01:57:37,436
Machine will find the lie.

987
01:57:38,745 --> 01:57:40,372
Aren't you ashamed to ask like that?

988
01:57:45,085 --> 01:57:47,315
When you're speaking truth,
why are you scared of a machine?

989
01:57:49,422 --> 01:57:51,549
l somehow managed to hold
my life for 14 days,

990
01:57:52,826 --> 01:57:55,056
but your mean words
are killing me.

991
01:57:56,763 --> 01:57:59,061
Truth sometimes is very mean.

992
01:58:00,100 --> 01:58:02,398
What is truth?
How would you know it is truth?

993
01:58:05,605 --> 01:58:06,401
He told me.

994
01:58:09,609 --> 01:58:11,406
Who? What?

995
01:58:14,114 --> 01:58:18,414
My hand is sleazy hand,
but your wife is not chaste.

996
01:58:19,185 --> 01:58:20,413
He said you're not pure.

997
01:58:22,722 --> 01:58:25,589
No...l don't believe it.

998
01:58:27,861 --> 01:58:29,089
He wouldn't have told that.

999
01:58:30,296 --> 01:58:33,265
He told me a lot more things.

1000
01:58:34,734 --> 01:58:36,599
Shall l give all details?
- Stop it.

1001
01:58:37,871 --> 01:58:39,270
Pull the chain, l'll get down.

1002
01:58:40,306 --> 01:58:41,364
Don't threaten me.

1003
01:58:42,876 --> 01:58:44,605
You're literally throwing me out.

1004
01:58:46,713 --> 01:58:48,840
You're lying and l don't like it.

1005
01:58:52,819 --> 01:58:55,185
l'm not lying.
- You're lying.

1006
01:58:58,491 --> 01:58:59,617
Lie is written all over your face.

1007
01:59:01,761 --> 01:59:02,887
Epitome of lies.

1008
01:59:05,632 --> 01:59:06,792
l can see it in your eyes.

1009
01:59:57,584 --> 01:59:58,846
You shouldn't have come back.

1010
01:59:59,719 --> 02:00:02,244
l shouldn't take you
to Veera's hideout.

1011
02:00:02,555 --> 02:00:04,682
But you want to meet him.

1012
02:00:07,694 --> 02:00:09,423
l don't know why you're here.

1013
02:00:10,430 --> 02:00:13,593
lf you've revenge in heart,
please go away.

1014
02:00:14,567 --> 02:00:17,798
The respect and affection he has
for you will remain intact.

1015
02:00:19,906 --> 02:00:23,706
Don't know when he'll come
and how long you've to wait.

1016
02:00:24,477 --> 02:00:27,207
l've kept food and water.

1017
02:02:06,414 --> 02:02:07,813
You've come back.

1018
02:02:14,589 --> 02:02:16,318
What did you tell him about me?

1019
02:02:16,924 --> 02:02:21,156
l'm breathless, ears are numbed.
l can't hear anything.

1020
02:02:41,616 --> 02:02:43,345
Am l the weapon to win over him?

1021
02:02:46,988 --> 02:02:48,353
l'm feeling dizzy with happiness.

1022
02:02:51,259 --> 02:02:52,351
Don't get angry on me.

1023
02:02:55,997 --> 02:02:57,294
What did you tell Dev?

1024
02:03:06,073 --> 02:03:08,371
What did you tell him?
Tell me.

1025
02:03:29,330 --> 02:03:32,299
Leave my hand.
Leave my hand...die.

1026
02:03:32,667 --> 02:03:34,225
Left him to die.

1027
02:03:37,538 --> 02:03:39,062
Hold firmly.

1028
02:03:40,708 --> 02:03:42,403
l can kill you for your wife.

1029
02:03:48,950 --> 02:03:53,580
For the same wife's sake
l can spare your life too.

1030
02:03:54,689 --> 02:03:56,589
Leave you or save you?

1031
02:03:56,958 --> 02:03:58,084
Leave you or save you?

1032
02:03:58,292 --> 02:04:02,251
Leave you or save you?
Shall l leave you?

1033
02:04:03,631 --> 02:04:05,496
Did you say anything
bad about me?

1034
02:04:08,469 --> 02:04:10,596
A good wife for a tough man.

1035
02:04:12,373 --> 02:04:13,601
Through the test of fire...

1036
02:04:15,242 --> 02:04:16,539
...pure gold.

1037
02:04:20,481 --> 02:04:31,688
We are sleazy men but never allowed
even wind to touch the pure gold.

1038
02:04:39,166 --> 02:04:40,463
Told him nothing else?

1039
02:04:44,171 --> 02:04:48,369
Go...take her away before
l change my mind.

1040
02:04:55,016 --> 02:04:58,577
Hold on to me...come up.
That's it.

1041
02:05:21,542 --> 02:05:23,737
Veera is happy, why are you sad?

1042
02:05:33,387 --> 02:05:36,015
Held you in captive for
14 days to scare him.

1043
02:05:39,393 --> 02:05:40,519
Just 14 days only?

1044
02:05:44,065 --> 02:05:45,692
Are 14 days so long?

1045
02:05:48,335 --> 02:05:52,533
Didn't feel so much when
l left you blindfolded?

1046
02:05:54,842 --> 02:06:00,041
But why am l so happy
on your coming back?

1047
02:06:11,092 --> 02:06:17,554
Please don't cry.
Stop!

1048
02:06:19,200 --> 02:06:20,394
l don't like women crying.

1049
02:06:31,512 --> 02:06:32,501
My life has come alive.

1050
02:06:35,449 --> 02:06:36,416
lt has started breathing.

1051
02:06:38,719 --> 02:06:40,243
Dev told me wrong.

1052
02:06:41,856 --> 02:06:43,483
He never listened to me.

1053
02:06:46,794 --> 02:06:48,261
Why did SP speak bad about you?

1054
02:06:52,399 --> 02:06:53,593
Without any reason?

1055
02:06:57,471 --> 02:06:58,495
Suspected me.

1056
02:06:58,739 --> 02:06:59,763
Suspected you?

1057
02:07:02,610 --> 02:07:03,440
SP?

1058
02:07:29,170 --> 02:07:32,298
Great...excellent!
- Dev is not here.

1059
02:07:34,742 --> 02:07:35,800
You're very smart.

1060
02:07:38,179 --> 02:07:39,646
He doesn't know l've come for you.

1061
02:07:40,548 --> 02:07:44,484
You know very well
who can lead you to me.

1062
02:07:46,587 --> 02:07:49,317
Come out. Come...

1063
02:08:24,325 --> 02:08:26,589
l told you l'll come back for you.

1064
02:08:28,762 --> 02:08:32,459
SP! Shoot me.

1065
02:08:33,567 --> 02:08:36,297
Shoot me....shoot me...

1066
02:08:37,571 --> 02:08:38,595
Shoot me!

1067
02:08:40,908 --> 02:08:43,468
Not just one shot, fire ten times.

1068
02:08:43,677 --> 02:08:44,871
Spray hundreds of bullets.

1069
02:08:45,346 --> 02:08:47,541
Shoot me....shoot me...

1070
02:08:50,851 --> 02:08:51,715
Ragini, move aside.

1071
02:08:51,919 --> 02:08:53,716
You can't kill my happiness.

1072
02:08:54,355 --> 02:08:55,219
Move!

1073
02:08:55,422 --> 02:08:56,719
You can't kill.

1074
02:08:58,525 --> 02:08:59,719
Move!

1075
02:09:34,895 --> 02:09:39,594
<i>l'll come back...</i>

1076
02:09:41,302 --> 02:09:45,762
<i>l'll come back again...</i>

1077
02:09:46,907 --> 02:09:57,613
<i>l'll follow you...</i>

1078
02:09:59,420 --> 02:10:05,052
<i>ls life nothing but the</i>
<i>scribbling of an infant..</i>

1079
02:10:05,659 --> 02:10:11,529
<i>ls learning the meaning of it,</i>
<i>the quest of life?</i>

1080
02:10:12,333 --> 02:10:16,895
<i>Life changes when we</i>
<i>understand its meaning...</i>

1081
02:10:18,605 --> 02:10:23,372
<i>The meaning changes</i>
<i>as our life changes...</i>

1082
02:10:24,345 --> 02:10:27,803
<i>A dream still floats in the air...</i>

1083
02:10:30,517 --> 02:10:34,044
<i>And smiling at me as it floats...</i>

